Shoreline.Edmonds Unitarian Universalist Church:
The Edmonds Unitarian Universalist Church (EUUC) in Edmonds, Washington is a Unitarian Universalist church.


== History ==
The Edmonds Unitarian Universalist Church was started in 1957 as the Sno-King Unitarian Fellowship (Sno-King is a reference to Snohomish and King Counties). Until 1959, the group met alternate Sunday evenings, but in 1959 they rented Edmonds Masonic Temple to allow space for Sunday school.
